{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"So I'm going to talk today about collecting stories"},{"time":4000,"text":"in some unconventional ways."},{"time":6000,"text":"This is a picture of me from a very awkward stage in my life."},{"time":10000,"text":"You might enjoy the awkwardly tight, cut-off pajama bottoms with balloons."},{"time":15000,"text":"Anyway, it was a time when I was mainly interested"},{"time":17000,"text":"in collecting imaginary stories."},{"time":19000,"text":"So this is a picture of me"},{"time":21000,"text":"holding one of the first watercolor paintings I ever made."},{"time":23000,"text":"And recently I've been much more interested in collecting stories"},{"time":26000,"text":"from reality -- so, real stories."},{"time":28000,"text":"And specifically, I'm interested in collecting my own stories,"},{"time":32000,"text":"stories from the Internet, and then recently, stories from life,"},{"time":35000,"text":"which is kind of a new area of work that I've been doing recently."},{"time":39000,"text":"So I'll be talking about each of those today."},{"time":41000,"text":"So, first of all, my own stories. These are two of my sketchbooks."},{"time":44000,"text":"I have many of these books,"},{"time":46000,"text":"and I've been keeping them for about the last eight or nine years."},{"time":48000,"text":"They accompany me wherever I go in my life,"},{"time":50000,"text":"and I fill them with all sorts of things,"},{"time":52000,"text":"records of my lived experience:"},{"time":54000,"text":"so watercolor paintings, drawings of what I see,"},{"time":58000,"text":"dead flowers, dead insects, pasted ticket stubs, rusting coins,"},{"time":62000,"text":"business cards, writings."},{"time":65000,"text":"And in these books, you can find these short, little glimpses"},{"time":69000,"text":"of moments and experiences and people that I meet."},{"time":71000,"text":"And, you know, after keeping these books for a number of years,"},{"time":74000,"text":"I started to become very interested in collecting"},{"time":76000,"text":"not only my own personal artifacts,"},{"time":78000,"text":"but also the artifacts of other people."},{"time":80000,"text":"So, I started collecting found objects."},{"time":82000,"text":"This is a photograph I found lying in a gutter in New York City"},{"time":84000,"text":"about 10 years ago."},{"time":86000,"text":"On the front, you can see the tattered black-and-white photo of a woman's face,"},{"time":89000,"text":"and on the back it says, \"To Judy, the girl with the Bill Bailey voice."},{"time":93000,"text":"Have fun in whatever you do.\""},{"time":95000,"text":"And I really loved this idea of the partial glimpse into somebody's life."},{"time":98000,"text":"As opposed to knowing the whole story, just knowing a little bit of the story,"},{"time":101000,"text":"and then letting your own mind fill in the rest."},{"time":103000,"text":"And that idea of a partial glimpse is something"},{"time":105000,"text":"that will come back in a lot of the work I'll be showing later today."},{"time":108000,"text":"So, around this time I was studying computer science at Princeton University,"},{"time":111000,"text":"and I noticed that it was suddenly possible"},{"time":114000,"text":"to collect these sorts of personal artifacts,"},{"time":116000,"text":"not just from street corners, but also from the Internet."},{"time":119000,"text":"And that suddenly, people, en masse, were leaving scores and scores"},{"time":123000,"text":"of digital footprints online that told stories of their private lives."},{"time":127000,"text":"Blog posts, photographs, thoughts, feelings, opinions,"},{"time":131000,"text":"all of these things were being expressed by people online,"},{"time":133000,"text":"and leaving behind trails."},{"time":135000,"text":"So, I started to write computer programs"},{"time":137000,"text":"that study very, very large sets of these online footprints."},{"time":140000,"text":"One such project is about a year and a half old."},{"time":142000,"text":"It's called \"We Feel Fine.\""},{"time":144000,"text":"This is a project that scans the world's newly posted blog entries"},{"time":147000,"text":"every two or three minutes, searching for occurrences of the phrases"},{"time":150000,"text":"\"I feel\" and \"I am feeling.\" And when it finds one of those phrases,"},{"time":154000,"text":"it grabs the full sentence up to the period"},{"time":156000,"text":"and also tries to identify demographic information about the author."},{"time":159000,"text":"So, their gender, their age, their geographic location"},{"time":162000,"text":"and what the weather conditions were like when they wrote that sentence."},{"time":165000,"text":"It collects about 20,000 such sentences a day"},{"time":167000,"text":"and it's been running for about a year and a half,"},{"time":169000,"text":"having collected over 10 and a half million feelings now."},{"time":172000,"text":"This is, then, how they're presented."},{"time":174000,"text":"These dots here represent some of the English-speaking world's"},{"time":177000,"text":"feelings from the last few hours,"},{"time":180000,"text":"each dot being a single sentence stated by a single blogger."},{"time":183000,"text":"And the color of each dot corresponds to the type of feeling inside,"},{"time":186000,"text":"so the bright ones are happy, and the dark ones are sad."},{"time":189000,"text":"And the diameter of each dot corresponds"},{"time":191000,"text":"to the length of the sentence inside."},{"time":193000,"text":"So the small ones are short, and the bigger ones are longer."},{"time":196000,"text":"\"I feel fine with the body I'm in, there'll be no easy excuse"},{"time":198000,"text":"for why I still feel uncomfortable being close to my boyfriend,\""},{"time":202000,"text":"from a twenty-two-year-old in Japan."},{"time":204000,"text":"\"I got this on some trading locally,"},{"time":206000,"text":"but really don't feel like screwing with wiring and crap.\""},{"time":208000,"text":"Also, some of the feelings contain photographs in the blog posts."},{"time":211000,"text":"And when that happens, these montage compositions are automatically created,"},{"time":216000,"text":"which consist of the sentence and images being combined."},{"time":219000,"text":"And any of these can be opened up to reveal the sentence inside."},{"time":223000,"text":"\"I feel good.\""},{"time":228000,"text":"\"I feel rough now, and I probably gained 100,000 pounds,"},{"time":231000,"text":"but it was worth it.\""},{"time":235000,"text":"\"I love how they were able to preserve most in everything"},{"time":238000,"text":"that makes you feel close to nature -- butterflies,"},{"time":240000,"text":"man-made forests, limestone caves and hey, even a huge python.\""},{"time":245000,"text":"So the next movement is called mobs."},{"time":247000,"text":"This provides a slightly more statistical look at things."},{"time":249000,"text":"This is showing the world's most common feelings overall right now,"},{"time":252000,"text":"dominated by better, then bad, then good, then guilty, and so on."},{"time":255000,"text":"Weather causes the feelings to assume the physical traits"},{"time":258000,"text":"of the weather they represent. So the sunny ones swirl around,"},{"time":260000,"text":"the cloudy ones float along, the rainy ones fall down,"},{"time":263000,"text":"and the snowy ones flutter to the ground."},{"time":265000,"text":"You can also stop a raindrop and open the feeling inside."},{"time":271000,"text":"Finally, location causes the feelings to move to their spots"},{"time":273000,"text":"on a world map, giving you a sense of their geographic distribution."},{"time":276000,"text":"So I'll show you now some of my favorite montages from \"We Feel Fine.\""},{"time":279000,"text":"These are the images that are automatically constructed."},{"time":281000,"text":"\"I feel like I'm diagonally parked in a parallel universe.\""},{"time":284000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":287000,"text":"\"I've kissed numerous other boys and it hasn't felt good,"},{"time":289000,"text":"the kisses felt messy and wrong,"},{"time":291000,"text":"but kissing Lucas feels beautiful and almost spiritual.\""},{"time":297000,"text":"\"I can feel my cancer grow.\""},{"time":300000,"text":"\"I feel pretty.\""},{"time":303000,"text":"\"I feel skinny, but I'm not.\""},{"time":306000,"text":"\"I'm 23, and a recovering meth and heroin addict,"},{"time":308000,"text":"and feel absolutely blessed to still be alive.\""},{"time":311000,"text":"\"I can't wait to see them racing for the first time at Daytona next month,"},{"time":314000,"text":"because I feel the need for speed.\""},{"time":316000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":319000,"text":"\"I feel sassy.\""},{"time":320000,"text":"\"I feel so sexy in this new wig.\""},{"time":323000,"text":"As you can see, \"We Feel Fine\" collects"},{"time":325000,"text":"very, very small-scale personal stories."},{"time":327000,"text":"Sometimes, stories as short as two or three words."},{"time":329000,"text":"So, really even challenging the notion"},{"time":331000,"text":"of what can be considered a story."},{"time":333000,"text":"And recently, I've become interested in diving much more deeply into a single story."},{"time":337000,"text":"And that's led me to doing some work with the physical world,"},{"time":340000,"text":"not with the Internet,"},{"time":341000,"text":"and only using the Internet at the very last moment, as a presentation medium."},{"time":345000,"text":"So these are some newer projects that"},{"time":346000,"text":"actually aren't even launched publicly yet."},{"time":348000,"text":"The first such one is called \"The Whale Hunt.\""},{"time":350000,"text":"Last May, I spent nine days living up in Barrow, Alaska,"},{"time":353000,"text":"the northernmost settlement in the United States,"},{"time":355000,"text":"with a family of Inupiat Eskimos,"},{"time":357000,"text":"documenting their annual spring whale hunt."},{"time":360000,"text":"This is the whaling camp here, we're about six miles from shore,"},{"time":363000,"text":"camping on five and a half feet of thick, frozen pack ice."},{"time":366000,"text":"And that water that you see there is the open lead,"},{"time":368000,"text":"and through that lead, bowhead whales migrate north each springtime."},{"time":372000,"text":"And the Eskimo community basically camps out on the edge of the ice here,"},{"time":375000,"text":"waits for a whale to come close enough to attack. And when it does,"},{"time":378000,"text":"it throws a harpoon at it, and then hauls the whale up"},{"time":380000,"text":"under the ice, and cuts it up."},{"time":382000,"text":"And that would provide the community's food supply for a long time."},{"time":384000,"text":"So I went up there, and I lived with these guys"},{"time":386000,"text":"out in their whaling camp here, and photographed the entire experience,"},{"time":389000,"text":"beginning with the taxi ride to Newark airport in New York,"},{"time":393000,"text":"and ending with the butchering of the second whale, seven and a half days later."},{"time":396000,"text":"I photographed that entire experience at five-minute intervals."},{"time":399000,"text":"So every five minutes, I took a photograph."},{"time":401000,"text":"When I was awake, with the camera around my neck."},{"time":403000,"text":"When I was sleeping, with a tripod and a timer."},{"time":405000,"text":"And then in moments of high adrenaline,"},{"time":407000,"text":"like when something exciting was happening,"},{"time":409000,"text":"I would up that photographic frequency to as many as"},{"time":411000,"text":"37 photographs in five minutes."},{"time":413000,"text":"So what this created was a photographic heartbeat"},{"time":415000,"text":"that sped up and slowed down, more or less matching"},{"time":417000,"text":"the changing pace of my own heartbeat."},{"time":420000,"text":"That was the first concept here."},{"time":422000,"text":"The second concept was to use this experience to think about"},{"time":424000,"text":"the fundamental components of any story."},{"time":426000,"text":"What are the things that make up a story?"},{"time":428000,"text":"So, stories have characters. Stories have concepts."},{"time":431000,"text":"Stories take place in a certain area. They have contexts."},{"time":433000,"text":"They have colors. What do they look like?"},{"time":435000,"text":"They have time. When did it take place? Dates -- when did it occur?"},{"time":438000,"text":"And in the case of the whale hunt, also this idea of an excitement level."},{"time":441000,"text":"The thing about stories, though, in most of the existing mediums"},{"time":444000,"text":"that we're accustomed to -- things like novels, radio,"},{"time":447000,"text":"photographs, movies, even lectures like this one --"},{"time":449000,"text":"we're very accustomed to this idea of the narrator or the camera position,"},{"time":453000,"text":"some kind of omniscient, external body"},{"time":455000,"text":"through whose eyes you see the story."},{"time":458000,"text":"We're very used to this."},{"time":460000,"text":"But if you think about real life, it's not like that at all."},{"time":462000,"text":"I mean, in real life, things are much more nuanced and complex,"},{"time":464000,"text":"and there's all of these overlapping stories"},{"time":466000,"text":"intersecting and touching each other."},{"time":468000,"text":"And so I thought it would be interesting to build a framework"},{"time":471000,"text":"to surface those types of stories. So, in the case of \"The Whale Hunt,\""},{"time":475000,"text":"how could we extract something like the story of Simeon and Crawford,"},{"time":478000,"text":"involving the concepts of wildlife, tools and blood, taking place on the Arctic Ocean,"},{"time":482000,"text":"dominated by the color red, happening around 10 a.m. on May 3,"},{"time":485000,"text":"with an excitement level of high?"},{"time":487000,"text":"So, how to extract this order of narrative from this larger story?"},{"time":492000,"text":"I built a web interface for viewing \"The Whale Hunt\" that attempts to do just this."},{"time":497000,"text":"So these are all 3,214 pictures taken up there."},{"time":501000,"text":"This is my studio in Brooklyn. This is the Arctic Ocean,"},{"time":505000,"text":"and the butchering of the second whale, seven days later."},{"time":508000,"text":"You can start to see some of the story here, told by color."},{"time":511000,"text":"So this red strip signifies the color of the wallpaper"},{"time":514000,"text":"in the basement apartment where I was staying."},{"time":516000,"text":"And things go white as we move out onto the Arctic Ocean."},{"time":519000,"text":"Introduction of red down here, when whales are being cut up."},{"time":523000,"text":"You can see a timeline, showing you the exciting moments throughout the story."},{"time":526000,"text":"These are organized chronologically."},{"time":528000,"text":"Wheel provides a slightly more playful version of the same,"},{"time":531000,"text":"so these are also all the photographs organized chronologically."},{"time":534000,"text":"And any of these can be clicked,"},{"time":536000,"text":"and then the narrative is entered at that position."},{"time":538000,"text":"So here I am sleeping on the airplane heading up to Alaska."},{"time":541000,"text":"That's \"Moby Dick.\""},{"time":543000,"text":"This is the food we ate."},{"time":545000,"text":"This is in the Patkotak's family living room"},{"time":548000,"text":"in their house in Barrow. The boxed wine they served us."},{"time":551000,"text":"Cigarette break outside -- I don't smoke."},{"time":554000,"text":"This is a really exciting sequence of me sleeping."},{"time":558000,"text":"This is out at whale camp, on the Arctic Ocean."},{"time":562000,"text":"This graph that I'm clicking down here is meant to be"},{"time":564000,"text":"reminiscent of a medical heartbeat graph,"},{"time":566000,"text":"showing the exciting moments of adrenaline."},{"time":571000,"text":"This is the ice starting to freeze over. The snow fence they built."},{"time":574000,"text":"And so what I'll show you now is the ability to pull out sub-stories."},{"time":577000,"text":"So, here you see the cast. These are all of the people in \"The Whale Hunt\""},{"time":581000,"text":"and the two whales that were killed down here."},{"time":583000,"text":"And we could do something as arbitrary as, say,"},{"time":585000,"text":"extract the story of Rony, involving the concepts of blood"},{"time":591000,"text":"and whales and tools, taking place on the Arctic Ocean,"},{"time":596000,"text":"at Ahkivgaq camp, with the heartbeat level of fast."},{"time":600000,"text":"And now we've whittled down that whole story"},{"time":602000,"text":"to just 29 matching photographs,"},{"time":604000,"text":"and then we can enter the narrative at that position."},{"time":606000,"text":"And you can see Rony cutting up the whale here."},{"time":608000,"text":"These whales are about 40 feet long,"},{"time":610000,"text":"and weighing over 40 tons. And they provide the food source"},{"time":613000,"text":"for the community for much of the year."},{"time":617000,"text":"Skipping ahead a bit more here, this is Rony on the whale carcass."},{"time":622000,"text":"They use no chainsaws or anything; it's entirely just blades,"},{"time":625000,"text":"and an incredibly efficient process."},{"time":627000,"text":"This is the guys on the rope, pulling open the carcass."},{"time":630000,"text":"This is the muktuk, or the blubber, all lined up for community distribution."},{"time":634000,"text":"It's baleen. Moving on."},{"time":637000,"text":"So what I'm going to tell you about next"},{"time":639000,"text":"is a very new thing. It's not even a project yet."},{"time":642000,"text":"So, just yesterday, I flew in here from Singapore, and before that,"},{"time":645000,"text":"I was spending two weeks in Bhutan, the small Himalayan kingdom"},{"time":649000,"text":"nestled between Tibet and India."},{"time":651000,"text":"And I was doing a project there about happiness,"},{"time":654000,"text":"interviewing a lot of local people."},{"time":656000,"text":"So Bhutan has this really wacky thing where they base"},{"time":662000,"text":"most of their high-level governmental decisions around the concept"},{"time":664000,"text":"of gross national happiness instead of gross domestic product,"},{"time":668000,"text":"and they've been doing this since the '70s."},{"time":670000,"text":"And it leads to just a completely different value system."},{"time":673000,"text":"It's an incredibly non-materialistic culture,"},{"time":675000,"text":"where people don't have a lot, but they're incredibly happy."},{"time":678000,"text":"So I went around and I talked to people about some of these ideas."},{"time":681000,"text":"So, I did a number of things. I asked people a number of set questions,"},{"time":684000,"text":"and took a number of set photographs,"},{"time":686000,"text":"and interviewed them with audio, and also took pictures."},{"time":688000,"text":"I would start by asking people to rate their happiness"},{"time":690000,"text":"between one and 10, which is kind of inherently absurd."},{"time":693000,"text":"And then when they answered, I would inflate that number of balloons"},{"time":696000,"text":"and give them that number of balloons to hold."},{"time":698000,"text":"So, you have some really happy person holding 10 balloons,"},{"time":700000,"text":"and some really sad soul holding one balloon."},{"time":704000,"text":"But you know, even holding one balloon is like, kind of happy."},{"time":707000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":709000,"text":"And then I would ask them a number of questions like"},{"time":711000,"text":"what was the happiest day in their life, what makes them happy."},{"time":713000,"text":"And then finally, I would ask them to make a wish."},{"time":716000,"text":"And when they made a wish, I would write their wish"},{"time":718000,"text":"onto one of the balloons and take a picture of them holding it."},{"time":721000,"text":"So I'm going to show you now just a few brief snippets"},{"time":724000,"text":"of some of the interviews that I did, some of the people I spoke with."},{"time":727000,"text":"This is an 11-year-old student."},{"time":729000,"text":"He was playing cops and robbers with his friends, running around town,"},{"time":732000,"text":"and they all had plastic toy guns."},{"time":734000,"text":"His wish was to become a police officer."},{"time":737000,"text":"He was getting started early. Those were his hands."},{"time":740000,"text":"I took pictures of everybody's hands,"},{"time":742000,"text":"because I think you can often tell a lot about somebody"},{"time":744000,"text":"from how their hands look. I took a portrait of everybody,"},{"time":747000,"text":"and asked everybody to make a funny face."},{"time":750000,"text":"A 17-year-old student. Her wish was to have been born a boy."},{"time":754000,"text":"She thinks that women have a pretty tough go of things in Bhutan,"},{"time":757000,"text":"and it's a lot easier if you're a boy."},{"time":765000,"text":"A 28-year-old cell phone shop owner."},{"time":767000,"text":"If you knew what Paro looked like, you'd understand"},{"time":769000,"text":"how amazing it is that there's a cell phone shop there."},{"time":774000,"text":"He wanted to help poor people."},{"time":783000,"text":"A 53-year-old farmer. She was chaffing wheat,"},{"time":786000,"text":"and that pile of wheat behind her"},{"time":788000,"text":"had taken her about a week to make."},{"time":790000,"text":"She wanted to keep farming until she dies."},{"time":794000,"text":"You can really start to see the stories told by the hands here."},{"time":797000,"text":"She was wearing this silver ring that had the word \"love\" engraved on it,"},{"time":800000,"text":"and she'd found it in the road somewhere."},{"time":807000,"text":"A 16-year-old quarry worker."},{"time":809000,"text":"This guy was breaking rocks with a hammer in the hot sunlight,"},{"time":813000,"text":"but he just wanted to spend his life as a farmer."},{"time":823000,"text":"A 21-year-old monk. He was very happy."},{"time":828000,"text":"He wanted to live a long life at the monastery."},{"time":834000,"text":"He had this amazing series of hairs growing out of a mole on the left side of his face,"},{"time":838000,"text":"which I'm told is very good luck."},{"time":841000,"text":"He was kind of too shy to make a funny face."},{"time":845000,"text":"A 16-year-old student."},{"time":850000,"text":"She wanted to become an independent woman."},{"time":852000,"text":"I asked her about that, and she said she meant"},{"time":853000,"text":"that she doesn't want to be married,"},{"time":855000,"text":"because, in her opinion, when you get married in Bhutan as a woman,"},{"time":858000,"text":"your chances to live an independent life kind of end,"},{"time":861000,"text":"and so she had no interest in that."},{"time":869000,"text":"A 24-year-old truck driver."},{"time":871000,"text":"There are these terrifyingly huge Indian trucks"},{"time":873000,"text":"that come careening around one-lane roads with two-lane traffic,"},{"time":877000,"text":"with 3,000-foot drop-offs right next to the road,"},{"time":880000,"text":"and he was driving one of these trucks."},{"time":882000,"text":"But all he wanted was to just live a comfortable life, like other people."},{"time":892000,"text":"A 24-year-old road sweeper. I caught her on her lunch break."},{"time":895000,"text":"She'd built a little fire to keep warm, right next to the road."},{"time":898000,"text":"Her wish was to marry someone with a car."},{"time":902000,"text":"She wanted a change in her life."},{"time":904000,"text":"She lives in a little worker's camp right next to the road,"},{"time":907000,"text":"and she wanted a different lot on things."},{"time":917000,"text":"An 81-year-old itinerant farmer."},{"time":919000,"text":"I saw this guy on the side of the road,"},{"time":921000,"text":"and he actually doesn't have a home."},{"time":923000,"text":"He travels from farm to farm each day trying to find work,"},{"time":925000,"text":"and then he tries to sleep at whatever farm he gets work at."},{"time":929000,"text":"So his wish was to come with me, so that he had somewhere to live."},{"time":939000,"text":"He had this amazing knife that he pulled out of his gho"},{"time":941000,"text":"and started brandishing when I asked him to make a funny face."},{"time":945000,"text":"It was all good-natured."},{"time":948000,"text":"A 10-year-old."},{"time":952000,"text":"He wanted to join a school and learn to read,"},{"time":954000,"text":"but his parents didn't have enough money to send him to school."},{"time":958000,"text":"He was eating this orange, sugary candy"},{"time":960000,"text":"that he kept dipping his fingers into,"},{"time":962000,"text":"and since there was so much saliva on his hands,"},{"time":964000,"text":"this orange paste started to form on his palms."},{"time":971000,"text":"(Laughter)"},{"time":974000,"text":"A 37-year-old road worker."},{"time":977000,"text":"One of the more touchy political subjects in Bhutan"},{"time":981000,"text":"is the use of Indian cheap labor"},{"time":984000,"text":"that they import from India to build the roads,"},{"time":987000,"text":"and then they send these people home once the roads are built."},{"time":989000,"text":"So these guys were in a worker's gang"},{"time":991000,"text":"mixing up asphalt one morning on the side of the highway."},{"time":994000,"text":"His wish was to make some money and open a store."},{"time":1004000,"text":"A 75-year-old farmer. She was selling oranges on the side of the road."},{"time":1008000,"text":"I asked her about her wish, and she said,"},{"time":1010000,"text":"\"You know, maybe I'll live, maybe I'll die, but I don't have a wish.\""},{"time":1018000,"text":"She was chewing betel nut, which caused her teeth"},{"time":1021000,"text":"over the years to turn very red."},{"time":1023000,"text":"Finally, this is a 26-year-old nun I spoke to."},{"time":1029000,"text":"Her wish was to make a pilgrimage to Tibet."},{"time":1032000,"text":"I asked her how long she planned to live in the nunnery and she said,"},{"time":1034000,"text":"\"Well, you know, of course, it's impermanent,"},{"time":1036000,"text":"but my plan is to live here until I'm 30, and then enter a hermitage.\""},{"time":1040000,"text":"And I said, \"You mean, like a cave?\" And she said, \"Yeah, like a cave.\""},{"time":1045000,"text":"And I said, \"Wow, and how long will you live in the cave?\""},{"time":1048000,"text":"And she said, \"Well, you know,"},{"time":1050000,"text":"I think I'd kind of like to live my whole life in the cave.\""},{"time":1054000,"text":"I just thought that was amazing. I mean, she spoke in a way --"},{"time":1056000,"text":"with amazing English, and amazing humor, and amazing laughter --"},{"time":1059000,"text":"that made her seem like somebody I could have bumped into"},{"time":1061000,"text":"on the streets of New York, or in Vermont, where I'm from."},{"time":1064000,"text":"But here she had been living in a nunnery for the last seven years."},{"time":1067000,"text":"I asked her a little bit more about the cave"},{"time":1070000,"text":"and what she planned would happen once she went there, you know."},{"time":1074000,"text":"What if she saw the truth after just one year,"},{"time":1076000,"text":"what would she do for the next 35 years in her life?"},{"time":1078000,"text":"And this is what she said."},{"time":1080000,"text":"Woman: I think I'm going to stay for 35. Maybe -- maybe I'll die."},{"time":1085000,"text":"Jonathan Harris: Maybe you'll die? Woman: Yes."},{"time":1087000,"text":"JH: 10 years? Woman: Yes, yes. JH: 10 years, that's a long time."},{"time":1090000,"text":"Woman: Yes, not maybe one, 10 years, maybe I can die"},{"time":1093000,"text":"within one year, or something like that."},{"time":1095000,"text":"JH: Are you hoping to?"},{"time":1097000,"text":"Woman: Ah, because you know, it's impermanent."},{"time":1099000,"text":"JH: Yeah, but -- yeah, OK. Do you hope --"},{"time":1105000,"text":"would you prefer to live in the cave for 40 years,"},{"time":1108000,"text":"or to live for one year?"},{"time":1110000,"text":"Woman: But I prefer for maybe 40 to 50."},{"time":1114000,"text":"JH: 40 to 50? Yeah."},{"time":1115000,"text":"Woman: Yes. From then, I'm going to the heaven."},{"time":1118000,"text":"JH: Well, I wish you the best of luck with it."},{"time":1123000,"text":"Woman: Thank you."},{"time":1124000,"text":"JH: I hope it's everything that you hope it will be."},{"time":1127000,"text":"So thank you again, so much."},{"time":1129000,"text":"Woman: You're most welcome."},{"time":1131000,"text":"JH: So if you caught that, she said she hoped to die"},{"time":1133000,"text":"when she was around 40. That was enough life for her."},{"time":1136000,"text":"So, the last thing we did, very quickly,"},{"time":1138000,"text":"is I took all those wish balloons -- there were 117 interviews,"},{"time":1141000,"text":"117 wishes -- and I brought them up to a place called Dochula,"},{"time":1145000,"text":"which is a mountain pass in Bhutan, at 10,300 feet,"},{"time":1149000,"text":"one of the more sacred places in Bhutan."},{"time":1152000,"text":"And up there, there are thousands of prayer flags"},{"time":1154000,"text":"that people have spread out over the years."},{"time":1156000,"text":"And we re-inflated all of the balloons, put them up on a string,"},{"time":1159000,"text":"and hung them up there among the prayer flags."},{"time":1161000,"text":"And they're actually still flying up there today."},{"time":1163000,"text":"So if any of you have any Bhutan travel plans in the near future,"},{"time":1166000,"text":"you can go check these out. Here are some images from that."},{"time":1170000,"text":"We said a Buddhist prayer so that all these wishes could come true."},{"time":1183000,"text":"You can start to see some familiar balloons here."},{"time":1186000,"text":"\"To make some money and to open a store\" was the Indian road worker."},{"time":1199000,"text":"Thanks very much."},{"time":1201000,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}